d/files/manager.go` | NewFileManager constructor |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/types.go` | FileManager interface, all request/response types, sentinel errors, constants |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/sanitize.go` | sanitizePath, parseFileMode, parseOctal |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/read.go` | ReadFile implementation |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/write.go` | WriteFile implementation |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/stat.go` | StatFile implementation |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/list.go` | ListFiles implementation |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/upload.go` | UploadFile + chunked upload + mergeChunks |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/download.go` | DownloadFile + range request support |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/delete.go` | DeleteFile (single + batch) |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/move.go` | MoveFile implementation |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/mkdir.go` | MkDir implementation |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/search.go` | SearchFiles implementation |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/chmod.go` | Chmod implementation |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/manager_test.go` | FileManager constructor tests |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/files/sanitize_test.go` | Path sanitization tests |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Existing JWT, Auth, and Middleware Patterns\n\n### 3.1 PicoD Auth (`pkg/picod/auth.go`)\n\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/auth.go`\n\nThe PicoD module has an **AuthManager** that:\n- Holds an RSA public key with `sync.RWMutex` for thread safety\n- Loads a PEM-encoded RSA public key from the `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable\n- Provides a Gin middleware (`AuthMiddleware()`) that validates JWT tokens\n\nKey code:\n```go\ntype AuthManager struct {\n    publicKey *rsa.PublicKey\n    mutex     sync.RWMutex\n}\n\nfunc (am *AuthManager) AuthMiddleware() gin.HandlerFunc {\n    return func(c *gin.Context) {\n        authHeader := c.GetHeader(\"Authorization\")\n        // Validate \"Bearer <token>\" format\n        // Parse JWT with RS256, require exp/iat, 1-minute leeway\n        // On success: wrap body with MaxBytesReader(32 MiB)\n        // On failure: HTTP 401 with {\"error\", \"code\", \"detail\"}\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 3.2 Router Auth (`pkg/router/middleware.go` + `pkg/router/jwt.go`)\n\n**Files:**\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/middleware.go`\n- `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/jwt.go`\n\nThe Router module has a more comprehensive JWT system:\n\n**JWTManager** -- generates AND validates tokens:\n```go\ntype JWTManager struct {\n    privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey\n    publicKey  *rsa.PublicKey\n    clientset  kubernetes.Interface\n    config     *JWTConfig\n}\n\nfunc (m *JWTManager) GenerateToken(claims map[string]interface{}) (string, error)\nfunc (m *JWTManager) ParseAndValidateToken(tokenString string) (jwt.MapClaims, error)\nfunc (m *JWTManager) TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(ctx context.Context) error  // K8s Secret persistence\n```\n\n**AuthMiddleware** (router) -- validates tokens and stores claims in context:\n```go\nfunc AuthMiddleware(jwtManager *JWTManager) gin.HandlerFunc {\n    // Extract \"Bearer <token>\"\n    // Validate via jwtManager.ParseAndValidateToken()\n    // On success: c.Set(\"claims\", claims)\n    // On failure: HTTP 401 with {\"error\", \"code\"} (string codes like \"UNAUTHORIZED\", \"TOKEN_EXPIRED\")\n}\n```\n\n**Additional router middlewares:**\n- `ConcurrencyLimitMiddleware(maxConcurrent int)` -- semaphore-based rate limiting (429 on overload)\n- `RequestLoggerMiddleware()` -- structured request logging with slog\n- `TraceIDMiddleware()` -- generates UUID trace IDs\n\n**JWTConfig:**\n```go\ntype JWTConfig struct {\n    Expiration time.Duration  // default: 5 minutes\n    Issuer     string         // default: \"agentcube-router\"\n    Leeway     time.Duration  // default: 1 minute\n}\n```\n\n### Key Differences Between PicoD and Router Auth\n\n| Aspect | PicoD (`pkg/picod`) | Router (`pkg/router`) |\n|--------|---------------------|----------------------|\n| Role | Token **verifier** only (public key) | Token **issuer + verifier** (full key pair) |\n| Key source | Environment variable `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` | Generated at startup, persisted to K8s Secret |\n| Error format | `{\"error\": \"...\", \"code\": 401, \"detail\": \"...\"}` | `{\"error\": \"...\", \"code\": \"UNAUTHORIZED\"}` (string codes) |\n| Claims extraction | No (only validates) | Yes (`c.Set(\"claims\", claims)`) |\n| Issuer validation | No | Yes (checks `iss` claim) |\n| Body size limiting | Yes (MaxBytesReader in middleware) | No |\n| Additional middlewares | None | ConcurrencyLimit, RequestLogger, TraceID |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existing design.md Files and Conventions\n\nThere are **28 design.md files** across the project. Key ones:\n\n### Root-level design.md (AR-016 -- PicoD File Management API)\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md`\n\nThis is the most detailed design document (1563 lines). Its structure:\n```\n# AR-XXX: Title -- Design\n## 1. Architecture\n   1.1 Purpose\n   1.2 Package Layout (ASCII tree)\n   1.3 Data Flow (ASCII diagrams)\n   1.4 Dependencies (table)\n## 2. Data Structures\n   - Config structs\n   - Interfaces\n   - Request/Response types (code blocks)\n   - Constants (table)\n   - Sentinel Errors\n## 3. API Contracts\n   - Route Table (table)\n   - Per-endpoint specs (endpoint, request, response, behavior)\n   - Error Response Format\n   - HTTP Status Code Matrix\n## 4. Core Implementation\n   - Constructor code\n   - Key function implementations\n## 5. Environment Variables (table)\n## 6. Testing Strategy\n   - Unit Test Matrix (tables per test file)\n   - Test Helpers (code)\n   - Mock Strategy\n   - Gate Requirements\n## 7. Deployment Considerations\n## 8. Implementation Steps (phased)\n## 9. Future Changes (table)\n```\n\n### AR-017 design.md (PicoD JWT Middleware -- stub)\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-017/design.md`\n\nThis is a **stub/placeholder** with TODO comments, following the same section structure as AR-016 but unfilled.\n\n### Other design.md files:\n| Path | Topic |\n|------|-------|\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-001/design.md` through `AR-017/design.md` | Per-change-request designs |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/ci-cd/design.md` | CI/CD pipeline |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cli-toolkit/design.md` | CLI toolkit |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/code-execution/design.md` | Code execution |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/deployment/design.md` | Deployment |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/idle-cleanup/design.md` | Idle cleanup |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/integrations/design.md` | Integrations |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/python-sdk/design.md` | Python SDK |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/sandbox-orchestration/design.md` | Sandbox orchestration |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/session-routing/design.md` | Session routing |\n| `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/session-store/design.md` | Session store |\n\n---\n\n## 5. go.mod -- Dependencies\n\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/go.mod`\n\n```\nmodule github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\ngo 1.25.0\n```\n\n### Direct dependencies:\n| Module | Version | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.10.0 | HTTP framework |\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.2.1 | JWT parsing/validation (RS256) |\n| `github.com/google/uuid` | v1.6.0 | UUID generation (trace IDs) |\n| `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | v1.22.0 | Metrics |\n| `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` | v9.18.0 | Redis client |\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | v1.0.73 | Valkey client |\n| `github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2` | v2.37.0 | Redis mock for testing |\n| `github.com/stretchr/testify` | v1.11.1 | Testing assertions |\n| `k8s.io/api` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes API types |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes apimachinery |\n| `k8s.io/client-go` | v0.34.1 | Kubernetes client |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | v2.130.1 | Structured logging |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | v0.22.2 | Controller runtime |\n\n### Notable indirect dependencies:\n- `golang.org/x/crypto` v0.48.0 (crypto primitives)\n- `golang.org/x/oauth2` v0.27.0 (OAuth2)\n- `google.golang.org/protobuf` v1.36.5 (protobuf)\n\n---\n\n## 6. All Authentication/Token-Related Code\n\n### 6.1 Constants\n\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/types.go`\n```go\nconst (\n    TimeoutExitCode = 124\n    MaxBodySize     = 32 << 20        // 33554432 bytes (32 MiB)\n    PublicKeyEnvVar = \"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"\n    maxFileMode     = 0777\n)\n```\n\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/jwt.go`\n```go\nconst (\n    rsaKeySize         = 2048\n    jwtExpiration      = 5 * time.Minute\n    IdentitySecretName = \"picod-router-identity\"\n    PrivateKeyDataKey  = \"private.pem\"\n    PublicKeyDataKey   = \"public.pem\"\n)\n```\n\n### 6.2 PicoD AuthManager (token verification only)\n\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/auth.go`\n- `AuthManager` struct with `publicKey *rsa.PublicKey` and `mutex sync.RWMutex`\n- `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` -- reads PEM from env var\n- `AuthMiddleware()` -- Gin middleware: validates Bearer token with RS256, requires exp/iat claims, 1-minute leeway, wraps body with MaxBytesReader\n- `newAuthManager()` -- constructor\n- `checkFatal()` -- helper for fatal exit on key load failure\n\n### 6.3 Router JWTManager (token issuance + verification)\n\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/jwt.go`\n- `JWTManager` struct with `privateKey`, `publicKey`, `clientset`, `config`\n- `NewJWTManager()` -- generates 2048-bit RSA key pair\n- `GenerateToken(claims)` -- signs with RS256, adds exp/iat/iss\n- `ParseAndValidateToken(tokenString)` -- validates signature, expiration, issuer\n- `TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret()` -- persists/loads keys from K8s Secret\n- `loadPrivateKeyPEM()` -- loads private key from PEM data\n\n### 6.4 Router AuthMiddleware\n\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/router/middleware.go`\n- `AuthMiddleware(jwtManager)` -- validates Bearer token, stores claims in `c.Set(\"claims\", claims)`\n- `ConcurrencyLimitMiddleware(maxConcurrent)` -- rate limiting\n- `RequestLoggerMiddleware()` -- request logging\n- `TraceIDMiddleware()` -- trace ID generation\n\n### 6.5 Server Integration\n\n**PicoD Server** (`pkg/picod/server.go`):\n```go\nfunc NewServer(config Config) *Server {\n    authManager := newAuthManager()\n    if err := authManager.LoadPublicKeyFromEnv(); err != nil {\n        checkFatal(err)\n    }\n    // ...\n    api := s.engine.Group(\"/api\")\n    api.Use(s.authManager.AuthMiddleware())\n    // /health is outside /api group, no auth required\n}\n```\n\n**Router Server** (`pkg/router/server.go`):\n```go\nfunc NewServer(config *Config) (*Server, error) {\n    jwtManager, err := NewJWTManager(jwtConfig)\n    jwtManager.TryStoreOrLoadJWTKeySecret(context.Background())\n    // ...\n    v1 := s.engine.Group(\"/v1\")\n    v1.Use(AuthMiddleware(s.jwtManager))\n    v1.Use(ConcurrencyLimitMiddleware(s.config.MaxConcurrentRequests))\n}\n```\n\n### 6.6 Test Helpers for Auth\n\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/auth_test.go`\n- `generateTestPrivateKey(t)` -- generates 2048-bit RSA key\n- `generateTestPublicKey(t)` -- extracts PEM-encoded public key\n- `signTestToken(t, key, claims)` -- signs JWT with RS256\n\n**File:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/pkg/picod/execute_test.go`\n- `authedRequest(t, server, method, path, body)` -- helper that generates a valid JWT and makes an authenticated request\n\n### 6.7 AR-017 Change Request (PicoD JWT Middleware)\n\nThe AR-017 change request documents the JWT middleware implementation:\n- **Proposal:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-017/proposal.md`\n- **Delta Spec:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md`\n- **Design (stub):** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-017/design.md`\n- **Tasks:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-017/tasks.md`\n\nThe auth middleware is already **implemented** in the codebase (auth.go, auth_test.go, integrated in server.go). The AR-017 design.md is a stub that needs to be filled in.\n\n### 6.8 Authentication Flow (end-to-end)\n\nFrom `project.md` and the code:\n```\nClient --> Router (verifies client JWT)\n         --> Router signs new JWT (RS256, 5min expiry, for PicoD)\n         --> PicoD (AuthMiddleware verifies Router's JWT)\n```\n\nThe Router generates short-lived JWTs (5-minute expiry) that are forwarded to PicoD inside sandbox pods. PicoD validates these tokens using the corresponding RSA public key loaded from the `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_28773f163ffeBCYBQKcHdDuQu4","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775843937945,"end":1775844198434}}}}
