{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844206088,"sessionID":"ses_287741cd3ffecg6dlzzvIdu3mv","part":{"id":"prt_d78901db5001dN61gM8AiB2Epx","messageID":"msg_d7890086d001dccq54sN3CCx19","sessionID":"ses_287741cd3ffecg6dlzzvIdu3mv","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_d8e84690650541319c8c7190","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-017/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-017/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/picod\n4: **Language:** Go\n5: **Size:** S\n6: \n7: ## 目的\n8: \n9: 为 AgentCube PicoD 沙箱守护进程添加 JWT 认证中间件，确保只有经过 Router 签发的合法请求才能执行命令和访问文件。当前 PicoD 的所有 `/api` 端点缺乏认证保护，任何网络可达的客户端均可直接调用沙箱资源，存在严重的安全风险。\n10: \n11: PicoD 运行在每个沙箱 Pod 内部，负责命令执行和文件管理。由于沙箱网络可能被同一 Namespace 内的其他 Pod 访问，必须通过 JWT 验证请求来源为合法的 Router 实例，防止未授权的沙箱资源滥用。\n12: \n13: ## 范围\n14: \n15: ### 包含\n16: \n17: 1. **AuthManager 实现**\n18:    - `AuthManager` 结构体：持有 RSA 公钥和读写锁，支持线程安全的密钥访问\n19:    - `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()`：从 `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` 环境变量加载 PEM 格式的 RSA 公钥\n20:    - 启动时强制加载公钥，失败则 Fatal 退出（沙箱无公钥则无法安全运行）\n21: \n22: 2. **AuthMiddleware 中间件**\n23:    - 验证 `Authorization: Bearer <token>` 请求头\n24:    - 使用 RS256 算法验证 JWT 签名，拒绝 HMAC 等非 RSA 签名方法\n25:    - 强制校验 `exp`（过期时间）和 `iat`（签发时间）claim\n26:    - 配置 1 分钟时钟容差（leeway），容忍分布式系统中的时钟偏移\n27:    - 验证通过后，将请求 Body 包装为 `http.MaxBytesReader`（32 MiB 限制）\n28:    - 验证失败返回标准化 401 JSON 响应\n29: \n30: 3. **路由集成**\n31:    - 将 `AuthMiddleware` 应用于 `/api` 路由组（execute、files 等所有业务端点）\n32:    - 健康检查端点 `/health` 保持在路由组外，不受认证保护（供 K8s liveness/readiness probe 使用）\n33:    - 中间件顺序：`gin.Logger()` → `gin.Recovery()` → `AuthMiddleware()` → Handler\n34: \n35: 4. **单元测试**\n36:    - 有效 JWT 请求正常放行（200）\n37:    - 过期 JWT 返回 401\n38:    - 缺少 Authorization 头返回 401\n39:    - 非 Bearer 类型 token 返回 401\n40:    - HMAC 签名（HS256）被拒绝，返回 401\n41:    - Body 大小限制生效验证\n42: \n43: ### 不包含\n44: \n45: - Router 端的 JWT 签发逻辑（由 AR-011 覆盖）\n46: - K8s Secret 密钥管理（Router 负责存储，PicoD 仅通过环境变量获取公钥）\n47: - RBAC / 基于角色的权限控制（仅做身份验证，不做授权）\n48: - JWT 刷新 / 续期机制（token 由 Router 在每次转发时重新签发）\n49: - mTLS 或其他传输层认证\n50: \n51: ## 架构概要\n52: \n53: ### 认证流程\n54: \n55: ```\n56: Client --> Router (验证客户端 JWT)\n57:          --> Router 签发新 JWT (RS256, 5min 过期)\n58:          --> PicoD (AuthMiddleware 验证 Router JWT)\n59:               --> 验证通过: 执行命令/文件操作\n60:               --> 验证失败: 返回 401\n61: ```\n62: \n63: ### AuthManager 设计\n64: \n65: ```go\n66: type AuthManager struct {\n67:     publicKey *rsa.PublicKey\n68:     mutex     sync.RWMutex\n69: }\n70: ```\n71: \n72: - **公钥加载**：启动时从 `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` 环境变量读取 PEM 编码的 RSA 公钥，解析后存储。加载失败则 Fatal 退出。\n73: - **线程安全**：使用 `sync.RWMutex` 保护公钥访问，支持未来热更新场景（当前为启动时一次性加载）。\n74: - **验证参数**：RS256 签名、强制 `exp`/`iat`、1 分钟 leeway，与 Router 端签发参数一致。\n75: \n76: ### 错误响应格式\n77: \n78: ```json\n79: {\n80:   \"error\": \"<human-readable message>\",\n81:   \"code\": 401,\n82:   \"detail\": \"<technical detail>\"\n83: }\n84: ```\n85: \n86: 错误场景：\n87: - 缺少 Authorization 头 → `\"Missing Authorization header\"`\n88: - 非 Bearer 格式 → `\"Invalid Authorization header format\"`\n89: - 签名无效 / 非 RSA 算法 → `\"Invalid token\"` + detail 包含具体错误\n90: - Token 过期 → `\"Invalid token\"` + detail 包含 `\"token is expired\"`\n91: \n92: ### 路由结构\n93: \n94: ```go\n95: engine.Use(gin.Logger(), gin.Recovery())\n96: \n97: api := engine.Group(\"/api\")\n98: api.Use(authManager.AuthMiddleware())\n99: {\n100:     api.POST(\"/execute\", ExecuteHandler)\n101:     api.POST(\"/files\", UploadFileHandler)\n102:     api.GET(\"/files\", ListFilesHandler)\n103:     api.GET(\"/files/*path\", DownloadFileHandler)\n104: }\n105: \n106: engine.GET(\"/health\", HealthCheckHandler)  // 无认证\n107: ```\n108: \n109: ### 目录结构\n110: \n111: ```\n112: pkg/picod/\n113: ├── auth.go           # AuthManager + AuthMiddleware\n114: ├── auth_test.go      # 单元测试\n115: ├── server.go         # Server（注册 AuthMiddleware）\n116: ├── types.go          # 常量定义（PublicKeyEnvVar, MaxBodySize）\n117: └── ...\n118: ```\n119: \n120: ## 影响分析\n121: \n122: ### 直接影响\n123: \n124: | 组件 | 影响 |\n125: |------|------|\n126: | `pkg/picod/auth.go` | 新增：AuthManager、AuthMiddleware |\n127: | `pkg/picod/auth_test.go` | 新增：AuthMiddleware 单元测试 |\n128: | `pkg/picod/server.go` | 修改：Server 结构体增加 authManager 字段，NewServer 初始化 AuthManager，registerRoutes 应用中间件 |\n129: | `pkg/picod/types.go` | 修改：增加 `PublicKeyEnvVar` 常量 |\n130: | `cmd/picod/main.go` | 无影响：NewServer 已封装认证初始化 |\n131: \n132: ### 上游依赖\n133: \n134: | 依赖 | 用途 | 影响 |\n135: |------|------|------|\n136: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` (v5.2.1) | JWT 解析与 RS256 验证 | 已有依赖，无新增 |\n137: | `crypto/rsa` / `crypto/x509` | RSA 公钥解析 | Go 标准库，无新增 |\n138: | `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | HTTP 中间件框架 | 已有依赖，无新增 |\n139: \n140: ### 下游依赖\n141: \n142: | 组件 | 影响 |\n143: |------|------|\n144: | Router | 无影响。Router 已在转发时签发 JWT（AR-011） |\n145: | WorkloadManager | 无影响。负责将 Router 公钥注入 PicoD 环境变量 `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` |\n146: | client-go | 无影响。client-go 仅用于 CRD 操作，不直接调用 PicoD API |\n147: | 沙箱内 Agent | 无直接影响。Agent 通过 Router 代理访问 PicoD，不直接调用 |\n148: \n149: ### 风险评估\n150: \n151: | 风险 | 等级 | 缓解措施 |\n152: |------|------|----------|\n153: | 公钥环境变量未设置导致 PicoD 启动失败 | 高 | 设计预期：无公钥则不应启动；WorkloadManager 负责注入 |\n154: | Router 密钥轮换后 PicoD 仍使用旧公钥 | 中 | 当前为启动时一次性加载；密钥轮换需重建沙箱 Pod |\n155: | RS256 验证延迟影响 PicoD 吞吐 | 低 | 单次验证约 0.1-0.3ms，对沙箱内延迟影响可忽略 |\n156: | 时钟偏移导致有效 token 被拒绝 | 低 | 1 分钟 leeway 覆盖常见时钟偏移 |\n157: \n158: ### 与现有组件的交互\n159: \n160: | 组件 | 交互方式 | 影响 |\n161: |------|----------|------|\n162: | Router JWTManager | Router 使用 RSA 私钥签发 token，PicoD 使用对应公钥验证 | 共享同一密钥对，通过 K8s Secret 分发 |\n163: | WorkloadManager | 从 `picod-router-identity` Secret 读取公钥，注入 PicoD 容器环境变量 | 无影响。WorkloadManager 已有此逻辑 |\n164: | AR-011 (Router JWT) | Router 端 JWT 签发与认证 | 互补关系：Router 签发 → PicoD 验证，形成完整认证链路 |\n165: \n166: ## 备选方案\n167: \n168: ### 1. 环境变量 + RS256 验证中间件（✅ 选定方案）\n169: \n170: **做法**：通过环境变量传递 RSA 公钥，在 Gin 中间件层验证 JWT 签名。\n171: \n172: **优点**：\n173: - 实现简单，改动集中在 2 个文件（auth.go + server.go）\n174: - 与 Router 端使用相同的密钥对和验证参数，保持一致性\n175: - 无外部依赖，沙箱内无需访问 K8s API\n176: - 验证逻辑与 AR-011 Router AuthMiddleware 模式统一\n177: \n178: **缺点**：\n179: - 公钥仅在启动时加载，密钥轮换需重建 Pod\n180: - 环境变量传递公钥在日志中可能泄露（需确保日志脱敏）\n181: \n182: **决策**：采用。与现有架构最契合，变更范围可控（S 级），满足安全需求。\n183: \n184: ### 2. K8s Secret 直接读取\n185: \n186: **做法**：PicoD 启动时通过 in-cluster client 直接读取 K8s Secret 获取公钥。\n187: \n188: **优点**：支持密钥热更新，无需重建 Pod  \n189: **缺点**：沙箱容器需绑定 ServiceAccount 和 RBAC 权限，增加攻击面；引入 K8s client 依赖  \n190: **决策**：不采用。沙箱应最小化权限，不应直接访问 K8s API。\n191: \n192: ### 3. Unix Domain Socket 认证\n193: \n194: **做法**：PicoD 仅监听 Unix Domain Socket，通过文件系统权限控制访问。\n195: \n196: **优点**：无需 JWT，传输层安全  \n197: **缺点**：Router 与 PicoD 需在同一 Pod 内（当前架构满足），但无法支持未来跨 Pod 场景；与现有 HTTP 接口不兼容  \n198: **决策**：不采用。当前架构中 Router 通过 HTTP 转发到 PicoD Service，需保持 HTTP 接口。\n199: \n200: ### 4. mTLS 双向认证\n201: \n202: **做法**：PicoD 启用 TLS，Router 提供客户端证书。\n203: \n204: **优点**：传输层加密 + 双向身份验证  \n205: **缺点**：证书管理复杂；沙箱内 TLS 终止增加资源消耗；与现有 JWT 体系重复  \n206: **决策**：不采用。可在应用层 JWT 认证之上叠加，无需替代现有方案。\n207: \n208: ## 实现要点\n209: \n210: ### 常量定义\n211: \n212: ```go\n213: const (\n214:     PublicKeyEnvVar = \"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"\n215:     MaxBodySize     = 32 << 20  // 32 MiB\n216: )\n217: ```\n218: \n219: ### AuthMiddleware 核心逻辑\n220: \n221: 1. 提取 `Authorization` 头，校验 `Bearer` 前缀\n222: 2. 调用 `jwt.Parse()` 验证签名，KeyFunc 中检查签名方法必须为 `*jwt.SigningMethodRSA`\n223: 3. 使用 `jwt.WithExpirationRequired()`、`jwt.WithIssuedAt()`、`jwt.WithLeeway(time.Minute)` 选项\n224: 4. 验证失败统一返回 401 JSON，detail 字段包含具体错误信息\n225: 5. 验证通过后包装 `c.Request.Body` 为 `http.MaxBytesReader`\n226: \n227: ### Server 初始化\n228: \n229: ```go\n230: authManager := newAuthManager()\n231: if err := authManager.LoadPublicKeyFromEnv(); err != nil {\n232:     checkFatal(err)  // 公钥加载失败则 Fatal 退出\n233: }\n234: ```\n235: \n236: ### 测试策略\n237: \n238: - 使用 `rsa.GenerateKey()` 生成临时密钥对，公钥设置到 AuthManager，私钥签署测试 token\n239: - 覆盖所有错误分支：缺失 header、格式错误、过期、非 RSA 签名\n240: - 验证 Body 大小限制在认证通过后生效\n241: \n242: ## 验收标准\n243: \n244: 1. **认证中间件**\n245:    - [ ] `AuthMiddleware` 正确验证有效 JWT 并放行请求\n246:    - [ ] 过期 JWT 返回 401\n247:    - [ ] 缺少 Authorization 头返回 401\n248:    - [ ] 非 Bearer 类型 token 返回 401\n249:    - [ ] HMAC 签名（HS256）被拒绝，返回 401\n250:    - [ ] 验证通过后 Body 被 MaxBytesReader 包装\n251: \n252: 2. **公钥加载**\n253:    - [ ] 从 `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` 环境变量正确加载 RSA 公钥\n254:    - [ ] 环境变量未设置时返回错误\n255:    - [ ] 非 PEM 格式返回错误\n256: \n257: 3. **路由集成**\n258:    - [ ] `/api` 路由组受 AuthMiddleware 保护\n259:    - [ ] `/health` 端点保持公开，无需认证\n260: \n261: 4. **测试覆盖**\n262:    - [ ] 所有新增代码行覆盖率达到 80% 以上\n263:    - [ ] `go test ./pkg/picod/...` 全部通过\n264: \n265: ## 状态\n266: \n267: - [ ] 提案审查\n268: - [ ] 实现\n269: - [ ] 验证\n\n(End of file - total 269 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件\n\n**Module:** pkg/picod\n**Language:** Go\n**Size:** S\n\n## 目的\n\n为 AgentCube PicoD 沙箱守护进程添加 JWT 认证中间件，确保只有经过 Router 签发的合法请求才能执行命令和访问文件。当前 PicoD 的所有 `/api` 端点缺乏认证保护，任何网络可达的客户端均可直接调用沙箱资源，存在严重的安全风险。\n\nPicoD 运行在每个沙箱 Pod 内部，负责命令执行和文件管理。由于沙箱网络可能被同一 Namespace 内的其他 Pod 访问，必须通过 JWT 验证请求来源为合法的 Router 实例，防止未授权的沙箱资源滥用。\n\n## 范围\n\n### 包含\n\n1. **AuthManager 实现**\n   - `AuthManager` 结构体：持有 RSA 公钥和读写锁，支持线程安全的密钥访问\n   - `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()`：从 `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` 环境变量加载 PEM 格式的 RSA 公钥\n   - 启动时强制加载公钥，失败则 Fatal 退出（沙箱无公钥则无法安全运行）","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-017/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775844206080,"end":1775844206087}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844207267,"sessionID":"ses_287741cd3ffecg6dlzzvIdu3mv","part":{"id":"prt_d78902697001FncsWtn3kqRvXu","messageID":"msg_d7890086d001dccq54sN3CCx19","sessionID":"ses_287741cd3ffecg6dlzzvIdu3mv","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_4903ff417d9244dfa367b496","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `pkg/picod`\n6: - **Language:** Go\n7: - **Size:** S\n8: - **Base specs:** `deployment/client-go.md`\n9: \n10: ## Delta Requirements\n11: \n12: ### Requirement: AuthManager structure and public key loading\n13: \n14: The system SHALL provide an `AuthManager` struct that holds an RSA public key and a `sync.RWMutex` for thread-safe access. The `AuthManager` SHALL support loading a PEM-encoded RSA public key from the `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable.\n15: \n16: ```go\n17: type AuthManager struct {\n18:     publicKey *rsa.PublicKey\n19:     mutex     sync.RWMutex\n20: }\n21: ```\n22: \n23: `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` SHALL:\n24: 1. Read the `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable\n25: 2. Decode the PEM block\n26: 3. Parse the PKIX public key\n27: 4. Verify the key is an RSA public key\n28: 5. Store the key in the `AuthManager` under write lock\n29: \n30: If the environment variable is empty, the PEM block is invalid, or the key is not RSA, the function SHALL return an error.\n31: \n32: #### Scenario: Load valid RSA public key from environment\n33: \n34: - **GIVEN** `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` contains a valid PEM-encoded RSA public key\n35: - **WHEN** `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` is called\n36: - **THEN** the function returns no error and `publicKey` is non-nil\n37: \n38: #### Scenario: Missing environment variable\n39: \n40: - **GIVEN** `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` is not set\n41: - **WHEN** `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` is called\n42: - **THEN** the function returns an error containing \"not set\"\n43: \n44: #### Scenario: Invalid PEM format\n45: \n46: - **GIVEN** `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` contains `\"not-a-pem-block\"`\n47: - **WHEN** `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` is called\n48: - **THEN** the function returns an error containing \"failed to decode PEM block\"\n49: \n50: #### Scenario: Non-RSA public key rejected\n51: \n52: - **GIVEN** `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` contains a PEM-encoded non-RSA public key (e.g., EC key)\n53: - **WHEN** `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` is called\n54: - **THEN** the function returns an error containing \"public key is not RSA\"\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: AuthMiddleware JWT validation\n57: \n58: The `AuthMiddleware()` method SHALL return a Gin middleware function that validates JWT tokens in incoming HTTP requests. The middleware SHALL:\n59: \n60: 1. Extract the `Authorization` header from the request\n61: 2. Validate the header format is `Bearer <token>`\n62: 3. Parse and validate the JWT using RS256 algorithm\n63: 4. Require `exp` (expiration) and `iat` (issued at) claims\n64: 5. Apply a 1-minute leeway for clock skew tolerance\n65: 6. On success, wrap `c.Request.Body` with `http.MaxBytesReader` limited to `MaxBodySize` (32 MiB)\n66: 7. On failure, abort with HTTP 401 and a standardized JSON error response\n67: \n68: The error response format SHALL be:\n69: ```json\n70: {\n71:   \"error\": \"<human-readable message>\",\n72:   \"code\": 401,\n73:   \"detail\": \"<technical detail>\"\n74: }\n75: ```\n76: \n77: #### Scenario: Valid JWT token is accepted\n78: \n79: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT signed with RS256 using the matching private key, with `exp` in the future and `iat` in the past\n80: - **WHEN** a request is made with `Authorization: Bearer <token>`\n81: - **THEN** the middleware calls `c.Next()` and the handler receives the request\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Missing Authorization header\n84: \n85: - **GIVEN** no `Authorization` header is present\n86: - **WHEN** the middleware runs\n87: - **THEN** the response is HTTP 401 with `{\"error\": \"Missing Authorization header\", \"code\": 401, \"detail\": \"JWT token required\"}`\n88: \n89: #### Scenario: Malformed Authorization header\n90: \n91: - **GIVEN** `Authorization` header is `\"InvalidFormat\"` (not `Bearer <token>`)\n92: - **WHEN** the middleware runs\n93: - **THEN** the response is HTTP 401 with `{\"error\": \"Invalid Authorization header format\", \"code\": 401, \"detail\": \"Use Bearer <token>\"}`\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: Expired JWT token\n96: \n97: - **GIVEN** a JWT with `exp` claim set to 5 minutes in the past\n98: - **WHEN** the middleware runs\n99: - **THEN** the response is HTTP 401 with `\"error\": \"Invalid token\"` and `detail` containing expiration information\n100: \n101: #### Scenario: Non-RSA signing method rejected\n102: \n103: - **GIVEN** a JWT signed with HS256 (HMAC)\n104: - **WHEN** the middleware runs\n105: - **THEN** the response is HTTP 401 with `\"error\": \"Invalid token\"` and `detail` indicating unexpected signing method\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Body is wrapped with MaxBytesReader after auth\n108: \n109: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token\n110: - **WHEN** the middleware passes and the handler inspects `c.Request.Body`\n111: - **THEN** the body is wrapped with `http.MaxBytesReader` limiting reads to 32 MiB\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: Clock leeway tolerates minor skew\n114: \n115: - **GIVEN** a JWT with `exp` set to 30 seconds in the past\n116: - **WHEN** the middleware runs with 1-minute leeway\n117: - **THEN** the token is accepted (within leeway window)\n118: \n119: ### Requirement: Route protection with AuthMiddleware\n120: \n121: The Server SHALL apply `AuthMiddleware` to the `/api` route group. All routes under `/api` SHALL require valid JWT authentication. The `/health` endpoint SHALL remain outside the `/api` group and SHALL NOT require authentication.\n122: \n123: The middleware order SHALL be: `gin.Logger()` → `gin.Recovery()` → `AuthMiddleware()` → Handler.\n124: \n125: ```go\n126: api := engine.Group(\"/api\")\n127: api.Use(authManager.AuthMiddleware())\n128: {\n129:     api.POST(\"/execute\", ExecuteHandler)\n130:     // ... file management routes\n131: }\n132: engine.GET(\"/health\", HealthCheckHandler)  // no auth\n133: ```\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: /api routes require authentication\n136: \n137: - **GIVEN** the server is running with AuthMiddleware registered on `/api`\n138: - **WHEN** a request is made to `POST /api/execute` without an Authorization header\n139: - **THEN** the response is HTTP 401\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: /health endpoint is publicly accessible\n142: \n143: - **GIVEN** the server is running\n144: - **WHEN** a request is made to `GET /health` without an Authorization header\n145: - **THEN** the response is HTTP 200 with `{\"status\": \"ok\", \"service\": \"PicoD\", ...}`\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: /api routes accept valid JWT\n148: \n149: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT signed with the correct private key\n150: - **WHEN** a request is made to `POST /api/execute` with `Authorization: Bearer <token>`\n151: - **THEN** the request reaches the ExecuteHandler\n152: \n153: ### Requirement: Server initialization with AuthManager\n154: \n155: `NewServer(config)` SHALL create an `AuthManager`, load the public key from environment, and fatal-exit if loading fails. The `AuthManager` SHALL be stored in the `Server` struct and used during route registration.\n156: \n157: ```go\n158: authManager := newAuthManager()\n159: if err := authManager.LoadPublicKeyFromEnv(); err != nil {\n160:     checkFatal(err)\n161: }\n162: ```\n163: \n164: #### Scenario: Server initializes with valid public key\n165: \n166: - **GIVEN** `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` is set to a valid RSA public key\n167: - **WHEN** `NewServer(config)` is called\n168: - **THEN** the server is created with a non-nil `authManager` and routes are registered\n169: \n170: #### Scenario: Server fatal-exits on missing public key\n171: \n172: - **GIVEN** `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` is not set\n173: - **WHEN** `NewServer(config)` is called\n174: - **THEN** the process exits with a fatal error (klog.Fatalf)\n175: \n176: ### Requirement: Constants and configuration\n177: \n178: The following constants SHALL be defined in the `picod` package:\n179: \n180: | Constant | Value | Purpose |\n181: |----------|-------|---------|\n182: | `PublicKeyEnvVar` | `\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"` | Environment variable name for RSA public key |\n183: | `MaxBodySize` | `32 << 20` (33554432) | Maximum request body size (32 MiB) |\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: PublicKeyEnvVar has correct value\n186: \n187: - **GIVEN** the `picod` package is compiled\n188: - **WHEN** `PublicKeyEnvVar` is inspected\n189: - **THEN** its value is `\"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"`\n190: \n191: #### Scenario: MaxBodySize is 32 MiB\n192: \n193: - **GIVEN** the `picod` package is compiled\n194: - **WHEN** `MaxBodySize` is inspected\n195: - **THEN** its value is `33554432` (32 × 1024 × 1024)\n196: \n197: ### Requirement: Error response consistency\n198: \n199: All authentication failures SHALL return a consistent JSON error format:\n200: \n201: ```json\n202: {\n203:   \"error\": \"<human-readable message>\",\n204:   \"code\": 401,\n205:   \"detail\": \"<technical detail for debugging>\"\n206: }\n207: ```\n208: \n209: The following error scenarios SHALL be covered:\n210: \n211: | Scenario | error | detail |\n212: |----------|-------|--------|\n213: | Missing header | `\"Missing Authorization header\"` | `\"JWT token required\"` |\n214: | Bad format | `\"Invalid Authorization header format\"` | `\"Use Bearer <token>\"` |\n215: | Invalid token | `\"Invalid token\"` | JWT parse error message |\n216: \n217: #### Scenario: Consistent 401 for missing header\n218: \n219: - **GIVEN** any `/api` endpoint\n220: - **WHEN** a request is made without `Authorization` header\n221: - **THEN** the response is HTTP 401 with `{\"error\": \"Missing Authorization header\", \"code\": 401, \"detail\": \"JWT token required\"}`\n222: \n223: #### Scenario: Consistent 401 for invalid token\n224: \n225: - **GIVEN** any `/api` endpoint\n226: - **WHEN** a request is made with an invalid JWT (wrong signature, expired, etc.)\n227: - **THEN** the response is HTTP 401 with `{\"error\": \"Invalid token\", \"code\": 401, \"detail\": \"<specific error>\"}`\n228: \n229: ### Requirement: Thread-safe public key access\n230: \n231: The `AuthManager` SHALL use `sync.RWMutex` to protect concurrent access to the `publicKey` field. The `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` method SHALL acquire a write lock before updating the key. The `AuthMiddleware()` key lookup SHALL acquire a read lock.\n232: \n233: #### Scenario: Concurrent reads do not block\n234: \n235: - **GIVEN** a loaded `AuthManager` with a valid public key\n236: - **WHEN** multiple goroutines call `AuthMiddleware()` simultaneously\n237: - **THEN** all requests proceed without deadlock (read locks are shared)\n238: \n239: #### Scenario: Key update is thread-safe\n240: \n241: - **GIVEN** an `AuthManager` with a loaded key\n242: - **WHEN** `LoadPublicKeyFromEnv()` is called while another goroutine is validating a token\n243: - **THEN** no data race occurs (write lock blocks reads until complete)\n244: \n245: ### Requirement: Test coverage\n246: \n247: The auth module SHALL have unit tests covering:\n248: \n249: 1. Valid key loading from environment\n250: 2. Missing environment variable error\n251: 3. Invalid PEM format error\n252: 4. Valid JWT token acceptance\n253: 5. Expired JWT token rejection\n254: 6. Missing Authorization header rejection\n255: 7. Malformed Authorization header rejection\n256: 8. Non-RSA signing method (HS256) rejection\n257: 9. MaxBodySize wrapping verification\n258: \n259: #### Scenario: All auth tests pass\n260: \n261: - **GIVEN** the auth module is implemented\n262: - **WHEN** `go test ./pkg/picod/... -run Auth -v` is run\n263: - **THEN** all tests pass with exit code 0\n264: \n265: #### Scenario: Race detector finds no issues\n266: \n267: - **GIVEN** the auth module is implemented\n268: - **WHEN** `go test -race ./pkg/picod/... -run Auth` is run\n269: - **THEN** no data race warnings are reported\n270: \n271: ### Requirement: Code quality gates\n272: \n273: The codebase SHALL pass the following checks after AR-017 implementation:\n274: \n275: - `go vet ./pkg/picod/...` produces no warnings\n276: - `go test ./pkg/picod/...` passes all tests\n277: - `go test -race ./pkg/picod/...` reports no data races\n278: - No `log.Printf` usage (use `klog` for logging)\n279: - No sensitive data (keys, tokens) in logs\n280: \n281: #### Scenario: go vet clean\n282: \n283: - **GIVEN** AR-017 is implemented\n284: - **WHEN** `go vet ./pkg/picod/...` is run\n285: - **THEN** no warnings or errors are reported\n286: \n287: #### Scenario: All tests pass\n288: \n289: - **GIVEN** AR-017 is implemented\n290: - **WHEN** `go test ./pkg/picod/...` is run\n291: - **THEN** all tests pass with exit code 0\n292: \n293: #### Scenario: No race conditions\n294: \n295: - **GIVEN** AR-017 is implemented\n296: - **WHEN** `go test -race ./pkg/picod/...` is run\n297: - **THEN** no data race warnings are reported\n298: \n299: #### Scenario: No sensitive data in logs\n300: \n301: - **GIVEN** AR-017 is implemented\n302: - **WHEN** auth errors occur (invalid token, missing header, etc.)\n303: - **THEN** log messages do not contain JWT tokens or key material\n\n(End of file - total 303 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `pkg/picod`\n- **Language:** Go\n- **Size:** S\n- **Base specs:** `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: AuthManager structure and public key loading\n\nThe system SHALL provide an `AuthManager` struct that holds an RSA public key and a `sync.RWMutex` for thread-safe access. The `AuthManager` SHALL support loading a PEM-encoded RSA public key from the `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable.\n\n```go\ntype AuthManager struct {\n    publicKey *rsa.PublicKey\n    mutex     sync.RWMutex\n}","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775844207260,"end":1775844207266}}}}
